<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In the built in JSON encoder method _encodeObject() the property is ignored if the value is not set. This means that all properties which have NULL as value are not included in the JSON output.</p>

<p>If the built in encoder really behaves exactly the same as json_encode (like the documentation states) it would include all properties also the ones that have NULL as a value. Optionally an ignoreNullValues option could be added instead.</p>

